reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cute yet durable
reviews.reviewText: I love going on walks with this stroller.It looks and feels higher end.And the biggest thing for me is how sturdy the wheels are. We can take our baby on grassy areas and it never gets stuck.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Baby Loves Riding Around in this Stroller!
reviews.reviewText: This stroller is so roomy and my baby loves going for walks in it. He doesn't like feeling confined and would only tolerate a short amount of time in his other strollers. The stroller is easy to assemble and fold up. Only downsides are it is a little bulkier than I expected when folded up, and the cup holder falls off easily. I lost it almost immediately. The seller was responsive when I contacted them about replacing the cup holder and I was able to find an alternative to attach to the stroller.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Second stroller, worth it!
reviews.reviewText: I have a stroller already that I keep in my car but I bought this to use on our daily walks. I LOVE this stroller. You can switch directions for the seat, it lays out into a full bassinet for an impromptu nap. It’s super light so I can lift it with one hand up my front porch steps. It doesn’t have any storage except the bottom basket so I had to add a pouch but for what it is, it really is the best. I will be able to use this for a long time bc it isn’t restrictive to size of the child until he gets to be too tall, but probably not for at least 2 years old. Buy immediately!
